The paper deals with channel estimation in wireless communications, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The use of sparse structure and adaptive algorithms also suggests a potential connection to signal processing (cs.SI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the simulation results mentioned in the abstract suggest that multimedia (cs.MM) could also be a relevant sub-category.
